the API out, make sure the extension is doing what I want it to do.

00:07:32.320 --> 00:07:33.559
Does it take data appropriately?

00:07:33.559 --> 00:07:35.920
Does it return the appropriate response?

00:07:35.920 --> 00:07:38.239
Does it behave the way that I think it should behave?

00:07:38.239 --> 00:07:43.040
This is really nice because as an R or a Python developer, this means I never have to open

00:07:43.040 --> 00:07:44.079
Tableau.

00:07:44.079 --> 00:07:48.200
I can start from the beginning and I can go all the way through to a working, functioning

00:07:48.200 --> 00:07:53.559
extension of Tableau, but I never have to actually open Tableau to verify its behavior.

00:07:53.559 --> 00:07:57.119
If we look at the R extension, here's the R extension we published.

00:07:57.119 --> 00:07:58.119
We see a similar thing.

00:07:58.119 --> 00:08:02.040
We have a nice interface that lets us know how to use this from within Tableau, and we'll

