take a look at that implementation in just a moment, and I also have the ability like

00:08:05.519 --> 00:08:11.519
we saw on the Python side to test and verify the behavior of this particular extension.

00:08:11.519 --> 00:08:13.839
I can copy output data from somewhere else.

00:08:14.600 --> 00:08:17.959
I can drop it in here and I can verify that this is, in fact, returning the results that

00:08:17.959 --> 00:08:24.440
I would expect it to be returning given the function that I defined.

00:08:24.440 --> 00:08:29.040
Now if we look at how to do this within Tableau, we've tried to make this as easy as possible

00:08:29.040 --> 00:08:33.840
for somebody who maybe isn't an R or Python developer but is a Tableau user to be able

00:08:33.840 --> 00:08:38.760
to come in and use an extension that has been shared on a platform like RStudio Connect.

00:08:38.760 --> 00:08:42.719
In that case, a user might come in to this particular page, they'll highlight and copy

