on primarily here is I'm in Tableau, but I need to do something to my data that Tableau

00:10:59.119 --> 00:11:00.119
can't do.

00:11:00.239 --> 00:11:03.359
And in many cases that might be like something machine learning or machine learning adjacent.

00:11:03.359 --> 00:11:08.479
I need to do some sort of statistical procedure or analysis that Tableau just isn't fully

00:11:08.479 --> 00:11:09.960
equipped to do.

00:11:09.960 --> 00:11:13.719
And I've had good conversations with people at Tableau that have indicated to me, look,

00:11:13.719 --> 00:11:19.119
we're not trying to make Tableau a fully featured statistical analysis engine, and so these

00:11:19.119 --> 00:11:23.359
extensions are the way in which we can broaden the horizons of what Tableau is capable of

